The determination of the amount of sclerostin present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of strongyloides IgG antibody present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of terminal deoxynucleotidyl transferase antigen present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of bioavailable testosterone present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of transforming growth factor Beta 1 present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of TNF-alpha production inhibitory activity present in a sample.

label.value: Soluble Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor Type II Measurement

The determination of the amount of tartrate-resistant acid phosphatase 5b present in a sample.
The determination of the ratio of urate compared to creatinine present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

A rectangular socket or bony arch that connects the ends of the tibia and fibula to the talus.
A lymph node located adjacent to the lumbar region of the spine, along the right lateral aspect of the inferior vena cava.
A lymph node located anterior to the pericardium, posterior to the xiphoid process, and in the right and left cardiophrenic fat.
A lymph node located in the transverse fissure of the liver.
A lymph node located in the space between the portal vein and inferior vena cava, along the hepatoduodenal ligament.
A lymph node located in the thoracic cavity between the lungs. It is bordered by the carina of the trachea, lower lobe bronchus on the left and the bronchus intermedius on the right.

A muscle that originates from the lateral condyle of tibia, spans the upper two-thirds of the lateral surface of the tibia, and is attached to the first cuneiform and metatarsal bones of the foot. It is a dorsiflexor of the ankle and invertor of the foot.
An anatomical structure comprising of trachea, bronchi, and bronchioles that terminate with the alveolar ducts, sacs, and alveoli.

The portion of the quadriceps femoris muscle group that is underneath the Rectus Femoris muscle, spans and covers the upper two-thirds of the anterior and lateral surfaces of the femur, and inserts into the lateral border of the patella.

label.value: Early Treatment of Diabetic Retinopathy Study Eye Chart

value.value: A diagrammatic method to test visual acuity which incorporates the Bailey-Lovie layout in conjunction with Sloan optotypes, which was first used in the Early Treatment of Diabetic Retinopathy Study.
A diagrammatic method to test visual acuity and contrast sensitivity, which utilizes large letters (at a 20/60 acuity) that decrease in contrast from right to left and top to bottom.
A procedure in which the catheter is passed into a peripheral vessel (usually in the groin) for the purpose of angiography of the abdomen, hands, arms, feet and legs.
A diagrammatic method to test visual acuity that utilizes the Sloan optotypes and a 1.25% contrast level.
A diagrammatic method to test visual acuity that utilizes the Sloan optotypes and a 2.5% contrast level.
The average number in a group of values that represent the thickness of an object at varying points along an axis.
A description of the diagnostic criterion that the subject fulfilled in order to establish a medical diagnosis.
The anatomical location of the beginning or early stages of a disease.
The number of disease loci that are seen at the beginning or early stages of that disease.
An assessment of the latency of the N145 or N2 wave of the visual evoked potential assessment waveform.

label.value: N75 to P100 Peak to Peak Amplitude

value.value: The magnitude, or height, of the P100 wave of the visual evoked potential assessment waveform. This assessment calculates the height from the N75 negative peak to the P100 positive peak.
An assessment of the latency of the P100 or P1 wave of the visual evoked potential assessment waveform.

A measurement of the location, in degrees, of the flatter principal meridian on a 180-degree scale, where 90 degrees designates the vertical meridian and 180 degrees designates the horizontal meridian.
A number or range of numeric values on the log scale that measures performance, function, quality, or ability.

label.value: Number of Correct Eye Chart Letters

value.value: The integer that describes the number of letters correctly identified by the subject during an eye chart assessment.
A measurement of the extent of defect in vision caused by a mismatch of optical power between the cylindrical and horizontal meridians, resulting in sub-optimal reflection of light onto the retina.

A measurement of the extent of defect in vision caused by a mismatch of optimal power between the cornea and/or lens and the length of the eyeball, resulting in sub-optimal reflection of light onto the retina.

Protein E7 (98 aa, ~11 kDa) is encoded by the human papillomavirus type 16 E7 gene. This protein is involved in the modulation of the activity of both retinoblastoma protein and histone deacetylases in the infected host cell, which is associated with viral genome replication and host cell transformation.
